ng occasionally.\nThis should take 1 hour.Meanwhile, place the vegetables with the garlic in a stockpot or large\nsaucepan with the remaining oil.Fry gently until lightly colored, turning occasionally.Stir in the tomato puree and continue cooking until everything is golden\nbrown then pour the red wine.Reduce the liquid by boiling gently until it acquires a syrupy\nconsistency.Once the bones have a rich color, drain them of any fat using kitchen\npaper towels if necessary.Add them to the vegetables along with the water.Bring the water to the boil, skim off the scum that rises using a ladle,\nthen add the herbs, bay leaves and black peppercorns.Simmer very gently for about 10 hours, skimming off any further scum\nthat accumulates on the surface.Strain the stock by pouring the contents of the pan through a\nmusli-lines colander set over a large bowl. Discard the bones, vegetables and\nthe herbs etc.Wipe out the stockpot or saucepan and return the stock to the pan.Boil down again until reduced by half or until it has reached sauce\nconsistently, then add the crushed black pepper\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCool and use as required"}, "source": "products", "id": 2832}, {"name": "Creamy Pumpkin Sauce", "kcal": 353.0, "contains": ["Milk"], "may_contain": [], "details": {"ingredients": "Butternut Squash (424g of Butternut Squash per 100g), Cooking Cream (28.6%) [Fresh Cream (Milk), Fresh Cow's Milk, Milk Solids, Stabilizers (E401, E516, E450, E331), Vitamin D3.], Extra Virgin Olive Oil (22.9%) [Natural Extra Virgin Olive Oil], Gralic (11.4%), Olive Pomace Oil (7.3%), Salt (2.6%) [Natural Sea Salt From The Res Sea, Anti Caking Agent: E551, Iodine (15 40mg/kg Salt)], Black Pepper (1.8%)", "notes": "in frying pan, heat the oiladd the garlic and saute until fragrant&nbsp;add the roasted pumpkin, salt and pepper&nbsp;then add the cooking cream&nbsp;bring them to cook on low heat for 5 minutes, then transfer to food processor and blend them until smooth and cr