ep golden, after 45 seconds to a minute, use a slotted spoon to flip; cook until they _x0019_re deep golden all over.Doughnut holes cook faster. Transfer the doughnuts to the prepared plates or racks, and repeat with the rest of the dough, adjusting the heat as needed to keep the oil at 190°C.", "category": "Bakery", "fat": 35.0, "protein": 7.0, "carbs": 25.0}, "source": "products", "id": 3080}, {"name": "Quinoa, Feta & Corn Muffin", "kcal": 207.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Milk"], "may_contain": [], "details": {"ingredients": "Fresh Milk Full Fat (23.1%) [Fresh Cow's Milk, Vitamin A, Vitamin D3.], Bakery Flour (21.7%) (Wheat), Sweet Corn (15.9%) [Corn], Water (13.4%), Extra Virgin Olive Oil (7.7%) [Natural Extra Virgin Olive Oil], Feta White Cheese Analogue (7.2%) [Water, Vegetable Oil (Non Hydrogenated Palm Oil), Milk Protein Concentrate Powder, Skimmed Milk Powder, Thickeners (E1401, E1442), Milk Whey (Milk) Protein Powder, Salt, Firming Agent (Calcium Chloride), Microbial Rennet, Starter Culture], Eggs (6.3%), Quinoa Red (4.5%), Chives (0.38%)", "notes": "Preheat oven to 180°C and prepare either a silicone muffin tray&nbsp;Sift the flour into a large bowl and stir through the quinoa, corn, feta and chives. Combine the milk, egg, and oil in a large jug, add to the dry ingredients and stir until well combined&nbsp;Divide the mixture among the muffin holes evenly and bake for 20 min or until golden and cooked through. Allow to cool slightly before transferring to serve", "category": "Breakfast,Bakery", "fat": 11.0, "protein": 5.7, "carbs": 20.0}, "source": "products", "id": 3081}, {"name": "Cooked Red Quinoa Subrecipe", "kcal": 83.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "details": {"ingredients": "Water (75%), Quinoa Red (25%)", "notes": "Combine the quinoa and water in a medium pot. Bring to a boil, cover, reduce the heat, and simmer for 15 minutes.Remove from the heat and let it sit, covered for 10 more minutes.Fluff with a fork.", "category": "Grains and pul