 the salt. Give it light toss to coat. Now very, very lightly with your fingertips or with a pastry cutter, cut the butter into the flour. Be careful not to melt the butter. If it's warm where you are place it in the fridge for a few minutes to cool again.Whisk the remaining milk and the egg into the yeast mixture until well combined, then pour it into the dry ingredients.Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and chill in the fridge for 8-24 hours.Turn the dough out onto a very lightly floured surface, Roll it out to a large rectangle about 6mm / ¼ inch thick (about 27cm x 45cm). Fold, letter style in thirds (foldthe top over the middle third, then the bottom third over that).Repeat this roll and fold 3 more times for a total of 4 times, ending with a much smoother folded dough. The last roll and fold, the dough will feel much tighter - it's ok if you can't quite roll it out to 6mm / ¼ inch. Add a touch of flour if you see it sticking to the counter or your rolling pin at any point but try not to add too much.Chill for 1-2 hours to relax before rolling and turning into Danish pastries.", "category": "Bakery", "fat": 3.3, "protein": 6.4, "carbs": 27.0}, "source": "products", "id": 3193}, {"name": "Mixed Berry Filled Croissant", "kcal": 245.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Milk"], "may_contain": ["Soya"], "details": {"ingredients": "Food (42.3%) [Wheat Flour (Wheat), WATER, VEGETABLE MARGARINE {VEGETABLE OILS (PALM), WATER, SALT, VEGETABLE EMULSIFIERS (E471, E322), PRESERVATIVE (E202), ACIDITY REGULATOR (E330), NATURE IDENTICAL Butter Flavour, NATURAL FOOD COLOR (E160a), ANTIOXIDANT (E319)}, WATER, SUGAR, WHEY (Milk) POWDER (COW _x0019_S Milk POWDER), YEAST, Wheat Gluten, SALT, DOUGH CONDITIONER {Wheat Flour, VEGETABLE EMULSIFIER (E481), ANTI OXIDANT (E300), ENZYMES}, NATURE IDENTICAL BUTTER (Milk) FLAVOR {NATURE IDENTICAL AND NATURAL FLAVOURING SUBSTANCE, EDIBLE OIL, FLAVOUR SOLVENT (E1518), ANTIOXIDANT (E307), ACIDITY REGULATOR (E260)}, VEGETABLE EMULSIFIER (E471)], Fr