wning. They are done when they turn golden brown and become crunchy.Cool: Remove the seeds from the oven and let them cool on the baking sheet. They will continue to crisp up as they cool.Stovetop MethodHeat Skillet: Heat a dry skillet over medium heat.Add Seeds: Add the pumpkin seeds to the skillet in a single layer.Toast: Toast the seeds, stirring frequently, for about 5-7 minutes. They should turn golden brown and start to pop. Watch them closely to avoid burning.Cool: Transfer the toasted seeds to a plate to cool.", "category": "salads and cold appetizers", "diet": ["Vegan"], "fat": 19.0, "protein": 19.0, "carbs": 36.0}, "source": "products", "id": 3200}, {"name": "Oats And Nuts Mixture For Vegan Granola Bars", "kcal": 169.0, "contains": ["Peanuts"], "may_contain": [], "details": {"ingredients": "Oats Nuts (64.8%), Maple Syrup Natureland (13%), Peanut Butter Almawasim (9.7%) [Roasted Peanuts, Sugar, Fully Hydrogenated Soyabean Oil, Salt], Coconut Oil (6.5%), Natural Coconut Sugar KLF Coconad (4.9%), Vanilla Flavour (0.81%) [Vanilla Extract (Nature Identical), Propylene Glycol (Food Grade), Water], Salt (0.32%) [Natural Sea Salt From The Res Sea, Anti Caking Agent: E551, Iodine (15 40mg/kg Salt)]", "notes": "Pour the wet mixture over the dry ingredients in the mixing bowl. Use a spatula to mix everything together until the oats and nuts are evenly coated.Transfer the mixture to the prepared baking dish and use the back of a spoon or your hands to press it firmly and evenly into the pan.", "category": "Bakery", "fat": 12.0, "protein": 2.4, "carbs": 13.0}, "source": "products", "id": 3201}, {"name": "Wet Mixture For Vegan Granola Bars Subrecipe", "kcal": 479.0, "contains": ["Peanuts"], "may_contain": [], "details": {"ingredients": "Maple Syrup Natureland (36.9%), Peanut Butter Almawasim (27.6%) [Roasted Peanuts, Sugar, Fully Hydrogenated Soyabean Oil, Salt], Coconut Oil (18.4%), Natural Coconut Sugar KLF Coconad (13.8%), Vanilla Flavour (2.3%) [Vanilla Extract (Nat