e milk, cream, and the split and  vanilla  and pod in a saucepot over medium-low heat and gently stir.\nBring to a simmer. Place the yolks in a mixing bowl, beat them. \nAdd granulated sugar  and whisk until the mixture is combined.\nTo begin the tempering process, gradually ladle the hot milk and cream mixture into the mixing bowl one ladle at a time while whisking continuously.\nThe aim is to gradually heat the egg yolks to the temperature of the warm milk and cream so as not to curdle the eggs.\nWhen the temperature of the yolks is similar to the temperature of the milk and cream, whisk the contents of the mixing bowl into the\nsaucepot with the remaining vanilla cream.\nSwap your whisk for a flat-bottom spoon and continue to stir as you cook to 85 C. \nThe cr me anglaise will be thickened and should coat the back of a spoon.\nTest by swiping your finger across the back of the coated spoon. If the sauce is thickened, the swipe should remain and not be filled in\nby runny sauce. Strain the cr me anglaise through a chinois into a mixing bowl resting in an ice bath. Remove the vanilla pod and set aside for future use.\nWhisk to help cool to room temperature.", "category": "Sauces,dips,DRESSINGS", "fat": 13.0, "protein": 1.8, "carbs": 24.0}, "source": "products", "id": 3292}, {"name": "Sausage Kale Cornbread Muffin", "kcal": 237.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Milk", "Mustard", "Soya"], "may_contain": [], "details": {"ingredients": "Polenta Merchant Gourmet (40.4%) [Pre Cooked Ground Maize (100%)], Chicken (38.5%) [MECHANICALY DOBONED CHICKEN MEAT, SPICES (WHITE PEPPER, SALT, GINGER), GARLIC POWDER, Wheat Flour, CONCENTRATED Soya PROTIEN PRESERVATIVE (E250), CONTAINS (Soya, Wheat (GLUTEN), Egg & Milk (LACTOSE (Milk))], Kale (11.8%), Onion (10.3%), Cheddar Cheese (10.1%) [Pasteurized Cow Milk, Cheese (Milk) Culture, Salt, Fungi Rennet (Chymax), Color (Beta Carotene)], Fresh Milk Full Fat (10.1%) [Fresh Cow's Milk, Vitamin A, Vitamin D3.], Fresh Yogurt Full Cream Na