 and let it rise a second time, or proceed to shape the dough.\nLine two half sheet pans with parchment paper, preheat your oven to 220*C , and place a steam pan on the lowest rack of the oven \nScrape the risen dough out onto a lightly floured work surface. Using a bench scraper, divide the dough into four equal pieces.\nForm one piece of dough into a ball by folding the dough over itself. With floured hands, gently pat the dough into a rectangle, Fold the top and bottom of the longer sides toward the middle, and then pinch the dough together to form a log. Roll the dough over so that the seam side is on the bottom.\nWith floured hands, roll the ends of the dough back and forth until they are skinnier than the middle. Pick up the log and place it on the parchment lined baking sheet, and curve the ends around and pinch them together to form a \"purse.\" Pat the thicker part of the dough to flatten it to about 3/4 inch thick. Cover loosely with oiled plastic wrap. Repeat with the other 3 pieces of dough. There should be two \"purses\" per half sheet pan.\nLet the loaves rise until puffy, about 30 to 45 minutes.\nWhen ready to bake, brush the loaves with the egg wash and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Add one cup of boiling water to the steam pan just before baking the bread.\nBake the loaves, one pan at a time, for 15 to 18 minutes, until the bread is golden,", "category": "Bakery", "fat": 5.6, "protein": 8.8, "carbs": 37.0}, "source": "products", "id": 3380}, {"name": "Hazelnut Crossiant", "kcal": 435.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Tree nuts", "Eggs", "Milk", "Soya"], "may_contain": [], "details": {"ingredients": "Food (77.8%) [Wheat Flour (Wheat), WATER, VEGETABLE MARGARINE {VEGETABLE OILS (PALM), WATER, SALT, VEGETABLE EMULSIFIERS (E471, E322), PRESERVATIVE (E202), ACIDITY REGULATOR (E330), NATURE IDENTICAL Butter Flavour, NATURAL FOOD COLOR (E160a), ANTIOXIDANT (E319)}, WATER, SUGAR, WHEY (Milk) POWDER (COW _x0019_S Milk POWDER), YEAST, Wheat Gluten, SALT, DOUGH CONDITI