: {"method": "dry the liver by kitchen towel or tissue (DO NOT WASH AT ALL) by small knife from the corner, lift the thin transparent membrane and pull it gentlyclean the beef liver well from the veins or any blood spots then start slice it into very thin slices put it in strainer to strain all the excess blood"}}, {"id": 8809, "name": "Egyptian Kousa Mahchi", "kcal": 151.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Cut the tops of the marrow, hollow them out using a zucchini corerwash the marrow from inside wellstart filling the marrow with the rice mixture in pot, place the tomato saucebring them to boil, then drop the stuffed marrow and cook them on medium heat for about 45 minutes until cookedseason with salt and pepper if needed", "ingredients": "Natural Extra Virgin Olive Oil"}}, {"id": 8810, "name": "Dough For Aloo Pakora", "kcal": 84.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "cut the potato into julienne then in steel bowl, place all the ingredients mix them well until combined and become as dough"}}, {"id": 8811, "name": "Vanilla Frosted Doughnut", "kcal": 435.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Tree nuts", "Eggs", "Milk", "Soya"], "may_contain": ["Peanuts", "Sesame"], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Combine the milk powder and the water together. Heat the milk until it is warm but not hot, about 90 degrees. In a large bowl, combine it with the yeast. Stir lightly, and let sit until the mixture is foamy, about 5 minutes.Using a stand mixer fitted with a dough hook, beat the eggs, butter, sugar and salt into the yeast mixture. Add half of the flour and mix until combined, then mix in the rest of the flour until the dough pulls away from the sides of the bowl.Add more flour, if the dough is too wet, the dough will probably become too thick to beat; when it does, transfer it to a floured surface, and gently knead it until smooth. Grease a large bowl with a little oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl, and cover. Let rise at room temperature until it doubles in size, about 1 hour.Turn the dough out onto a well-floured surface, and roll. Cut out the doughnuts with a doughnut cutter, flouring the cutters as you go. Reserve the doughnut holes. Knead any scraps together, being careful not to overwork, and let rest for a few minutes before repeating the process.Put the doughnuts on two floured baking sheets so that there is plenty of room between each one. Cover with a kitchen towel, and let rise in a warm place until they are slightly puffed up and delicate, about 45 minutes. About 15 minutes before the doughnuts are done rising, put the oil in a heavy-bottomed pot or Dutch oven over medium heat, and heat it to 190°C. Meanwhile, line cooling racks, baking sheets or plates with paper towels.Carefully add the doughnuts to the oil, a few at a time, When the bottoms are deep golden, after 45 seconds to a minute, use a slotted spoon to flip; cook until they _x0019_re deep golden all over.Doughnut holes cook faster. Transfer the doughnuts to the prepared plates or racks, and repeat with the rest of the dough, adjusting the heat as needed to keep the oil at 190°C.Glaze the doughnut by dipping them donuts into strawberry frosting 1-3 times.", "ingredients": "Cow's Milk Fat, Bacterial Culture"}}, {"id": 8812, "name": "Assorted Olives", "kcal": 686.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"ingredients": "Green Olives, Water, Salt, Acidity Correctors: Lactic Acid And Citric Acid, Antioxidant: Ascorbic Acid\nOlives, Water, Salt, Color Retention Agents: Ferrous Gluconate\nOlives, Water, Salt, Lactic Acid"}}, {"id": 8813, "name": "Bulgur with Mushroom and Feta", "kcal": 215.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Milk", "Sulphites"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Rinse the bulgur and place in a large bowl. Stir in ¼ teaspoon of salt and a good grind of pepper, then pour over the boiling water. Cover the bowl with clingfilm and set aside for 20 minutes, until the liquid has been absorbed and the bulgur is soft. Drain, if there is any liquid left, and set aside.Meanwhile, put 2 tablespoons of oil into a large sauté pan and place on a medium high heat. Add the onion and fry for 7-8 minutes, until soft and caramelised. Add ½ teaspoon of cumin seeds and continue to fry for 1-2 minutes, until dark golden brown. Remove from the pan and set aside.Add another 2 tablespoons of oil to the same pan and increase the heat to high. Mix in the mushrooms and ½ teaspoon of salt and fry for 6-7 minutes, stirring frequently, until the mushrooms have browned and softened. Add the remaining ½ teaspoon of cumin seeds and the thyme and continue to heat for 1 minute, stirring continuously. Pour in the balsamic vinegar and continue to cook for about 30 seconds: it should reduce to practically nothing. Stir in the bulgur, onion, dill, feta and chilli flakes, until warmed through, then remove from the heat.Spoon the bulgur and mushrooms on to a large platter or two individual plates. Sprinkle over some extra dill, drizzle with the remaining oil and serve"}}, {"id": 8814, "name": "Lamb Raghfan", "kcal": 346.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Milk", "Celery"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "in serving platter, place the bread scoop the rice over the bread then top it with the lamb and sauce serve extra sauce on the side if required"}}, {"id": 8815, "name": "Rice for Raghfan", "kcal": 185.0, "contains": ["Milk", "Celery"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "in pot, melt the butter on high heatpour the broth and season with saltadd the washed and drained ricecover with aluminum foil and cook on low heat for 20 minutesfluff the rice", "ingredients": "99.8% Butter (Milk) Fat"}}, {"id": 8816, "name": "Lamb for Raghfan", "kcal": 432.0, "contains": ["Milk", "Celery"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "place the sauce in pot and brin