 fragrant, 30 seconds to 1 minute.Remove the beef cube from the marinade (reserve the liquid) and add to the pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned on all sides.Add the water, tomato sauce, reserved marinade, bay leaves, salt, and pepper. Stir to combine and bring the mixture to a boil.Reduce heat to a simmer, cover, and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours, until the beef is tender.Add the potato, carrot, and bell pepper pieces. Continue to cook for another 20-30 minutes, until the vegetables are tender.Season with salt and pepper to taste.", "ingredients": "Beef100% Grain Fed Black Angus Young Prime (YP) Marble Score And 3+ Meat Colour1B 3 Fat Colour0 3"}}, {"id": 9010, "name": "Lumpiang Sariwa (Fresh Lumpia)", "kcal": 130.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Peanuts", "Eggs", "Fish", "Soya"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Prepare the filling by heating the oil in a pan.Sauté onion and garlic until onion becomes soft and transparent.Add sweet potato. Stir. Pour water and let boil.Remove the cover and let water evaporate. Add tofu dice, Stir. fry for a minute.Add cabbage, green beans, and carrot. Continue to stir fry for 3 minutes.Season with fish sauce and ground black pepper. Set aside.Meanwhile, make the fresh lumpia wrapper by beating the eggs in a large bowl. Pour oil and water. Whisk until all ingredients are blended.Slowly whisk-in flour into the mixture. Continue to whisk until all ingredients are well blended.Heat a non-stick pan. Lightly grease with oil or spray cooking oil.Scoop around 7 to 8 tablespoons of the lumpia wrapper mixture and pour into the pan. Swirl the pan to spread the mixture. Continue to cook in medium heat for 1 minute or until the wrapper is cooked. Note: the fresh lumpia wrapper is done when it gets unstuck from the pan.Remove the fresh lumpia wrapper from the pan. Arrange in a plate. Set aside.Prepare the Lumpiang Sariwa Sauce by boiling water in a saucepan. Add soy sauce, brown sugar and garlic. Stir.Dilute cornstarch in 3 tablespoons water. Pour the mixture into the saucepan. Stir and continue to cook until the sauce thickens.Assemble the fresh lumpia (lumpiang sariwa) by laying a piece of wrapper flat on a large plate. Put a piece of lettuce leaf in the middle of the wrapper and top with the fresh lumpia filling and chopped parsley. Secure the filling by folding the lower part of the wrapper upwards until it reaches the filling and then fold the sides inwards. Arrange each piece on a plate and top with lumpia sauce and sprinkle some crushed peanuts."}}, {"id": 9011, "name": "Beef Bulalo", "kcal": 147.0, "contains": ["Fish"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a large pot, combine beef shanks or osso buco and enough cold water to cover. Bring to a boil.Drain beef and rinse under cold water to remove impurities. Discard the liquid and rinse the pot.In the pot, return meat and enough cold water to cover. Bring to a boil, skimming scum that accumulates on top.When the broth has cleared, add onions, fish sauce, and peppercorns.Lower heat, cover, and cook at a bare simmer for about 1 ½ to 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender but not falling apart.Add corn and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until corn is tender.Add the Bok choy and green onions and cook for about 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender.Season with salt to taste. Serve hot with dipping sauce (fish sauce, calamansi &amp; slice red chili)", "ingredients": "Bok Choy Lettuce"}}, {"id": 9012, "name": "Ginisang Ampalaya (Sauteed Bitter Gourd)", "kcal": 81.0, "contains": ["Eggs"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Place the bitter gourd in a large bowlAdd salt and lukewarm water then leave for 5 minutesPlace the bitter gourd in a cheesecloth then squeeze tightly until all liquid dripsHeat the pan and place the cooking oilSautee the garlic, onion, and tomatoAdd the bitter gourd mix well with the other ingredientsPut-in salt and pepper to tasteBeat the eggs and pour over the bitter gourd then let the eggs cook partially"}}, {"id": 9013, "name": "Tortang Talong ( Eggplant Omelette)", "kcal": 59.0, "contains": ["Eggs"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Grill the eggplant until the color of skin turns almost blackLet the eggplant cool for a while then peel off the skin. Set aside.Crack the eggs and place in a bowlAdd salt and pepper then beatPlace the eggplant on a flat surface and flatten using a fork.Dip the flattened eggplant in the beaten egg mixtureHeat the pan and pour the cooking oilFry the eggplant (that was dipped in the beaten mixture). Makes sure that both sides are cooked. Frying time will take you about 3 to 4 minutes per side on medium heat."}}, {"id": 9014, "name": "Chicken Afritada", "kcal": 112.0, "contains": ["Fish"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Cut the chicken leg by 2 and set aside. In a pot heat the oil, add onion and garlic for a minute. Add the chicken &amp; fish sauce, cook for 3 minutes until light brown, add the potato &amp; carrot stir for a minute, then add tomato peeled and tomato paste, stir until well combined, add the water, cover the pot and adjust the heat into medium, cook for 20 minutes then add the green peas and cook for another 2 minutes seasoned with salt &amp; pepper.", "ingredients": "Chicken Whole Legs"}}, {"id": 9015, "name": "Inihaw na Isda (Stuffed Grilled Fish)", "kcal": 57.0, "contains": ["Fish"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Mix tomato, onion, white radish, salt &amp; crushed pepper until well combined, fill the seabream with the mixture and roll in banana leaf. Baked for 20 minutes 180'c."}}, {"id": 9016, "name": "Fish Paksiw", "kcal": 73.0, "contains": ["Fish"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Heat pot then pour-in vinegar and water, add salt and black peppercorn, bring to boil.Arrange the in the pan along with the ginger, garlic, onion, bitter gourd, eggplant, and finger chili.Cover and simmer in medium heat from 12 to 15 minutes."}}, {"id": 9017, "name": "Lumpia (Chicken Shanghai)", "kcal": 166.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Molluscs", "Celery", "Soya"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Heat oil in skillet, sauteed onion, celery &amp; carrot for a minute, Add the minced chicken, Seasoned with salt and pepper. then add soy sauce &amp; oyster sauce, cooked for 3 minutes, removed from stoves and cool it down, then add 1 egg to the chicken mixture and mix until well combined. Spoon the filling to spring roll wrapper and roll it.Fried the lumpia until the color turning golden brown."}}, {"id": 9018, "name": "Beef Boerewors Sausage Mixture New Recipe", "kcal": 201.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a mixing bowl, mix all ingredients until well combined"}}, {"id": 9019, "name": "Beef Boerewors Mixture New Recipe", "kcal": 169.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "\"Mix all ingredients in a bowl, then mince through a 5 mm plate"}}, {"id": 9020, "name": "Beef Bratwurst Sausage Mixture New Recipe", "kcal": 202.0, "contains": ["Sesame"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Mix all ingredients in a bowl until well combined"}}, {"id": 9021, "name": "Lamb Bratwurst Sausage Mixture New Recipe", "kcal": 275.0, "contains": ["Sesame"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Mix all ingredients in a bowl until well combined"}}, {"id": 9022, "name": "Chicken Bratwurst Sausage Mixture New Recipe", "kcal": 189.0, "contains": ["Sesame"], "may_contain": ["Gluten"], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Mix all ingredients in a bowl until well combined."}}, {"id": 9023, "name": "Chicken Bratwurst Mixture New Recipe", "kcal": 179.0, "contains": ["Sesame"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a mixing bowl, 