hite wine while the tomatoes sauce is cooking.\n\nAdd\nthe pickled jalapeños, raisins, olives and capers and cook until the flavors\ncombine, about 4 minutes.\n\nSeason\nthe sauce with salt and pepper.\n\nTo\nbake the fish, add some sauce to the bottom of an oven dish, then place the\nfish and cover it with the rest of the sauce.\n\nBake\nthe fish for about 15 minutes or until the fish is cooked.\n\nServe\ngarnished with the parsley.", "ingredients": "Natural Extra Virgin Olive Oil"}}, {"id": 9121, "name": "Albondigas (Spanish Meatballs)", "kcal": 75.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "To\nmake the albondigas sauce, place the oil in a saucepan over a medium heat then\nfry the onions, garlic and peppers together with the bay leaves and thyme.\n\nAdd\nthe smoked paprika, dried red chili flakes and tomato purée and cook out, then add\nthe tomatoes.\n\nCook\ngently for around 1 hour until thick.\n\nSeason\nwell with salt and black pepper.Serve\nwith the albondigas sauce over the meatballs and garnish with the parsley.", "ingredients": "Natural Extra Virgin Olive Oil"}}, {"id": 9122, "name": "Berejenas Rellenas (Stuffed Aubergines)", "kcal": 136.0, "contains": ["Milk"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Preheat\nthe oven to 150°C.\n\nWash\nthe eggplants, then cut them in half lengthwise.\n\nPlace\nthem on a baking sheet and score the flesh in a crosshatched pattern, being\ncareful not to cut through the skin.\n\nDrizzle\nwith a generous amount of oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.\n\nBake\nfor 25-30 minutes, or until flesh is tender, but don't overcook them.\n\nLet\nthem rest for 15 minutes once cooked.\n\nHeat\noil in a pan until hot, then sauté the onion, pepper, and garlic until\nsoftened.\n\nOnce\nthe eggplants are cool, scoop out the flesh from the middle of each eggplant\nand add it to the pan with the vegetables.\n\nWhen\nthe vegetables are starting to brown slightly, add the lamb and sauté until\ncooked through.\n\nSeason\nto taste with salt and pepper, then remove from the heat and let it rest.\n\nTo\nfill the skins, spread a layer of tomato sauce in the empty skins at the bottom,\n\n\nthen\nfill each one to the top with the meat mixture.\n\nCover\nwith grated mozzarella cheese.\n\nAdd\nthe eggplants to a roasting tray and place in a hot oven until the cheese is\nbrowned on the top, then let them rest for about 5 minutes before serving.\n\nServe\ngarnished with the parsley.", "ingredients": "Natural Extra Virgin Olive Oil"}}, {"id": 9123, "name": "Short Ribs in Black Pepper Sauce", "kcal": 163.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Molluscs", "Celery", "Soya", "Sulphites"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Heat\nthe oil in a wok over medium heat.\n\nAdd\nthe garlic and onion and stir-fry until fragrant.\n\nAdd\nthe bell peppers and continue stir-frying for a few minutes.\n\nIn\na small bowl, mix together the oyster sauce, soy sauce, black pepper, sugar,\nand beef stock.\n\nPour\nthe sauce mixture into the wok and bring to a simmer.\n\nCook\nfor 2-3 minutes.\n\nIn\na separate bowl, dissolve the cornstarch in water.\n\nAdd\nthe cornstarch to the wok and stir until the sauce thickens.\n\nThen\nadd the cooked beef short rib chunks to the sauce, heat through while tossing\nwell.\n\nGarnish with the\nspring onions and serve immediately"}}, {"id": 9124, "name": "Baked Potato Soup with Chives & Sour Cream", "kcal": 140.0, "contains": ["Milk", "Celery"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Fry the onion and garlic in the oil\nuntil soft.\n\nPour the stock into the pan, and\nthen add the potatoes, salt and freshly ground white pepper and bay leaf.\n\nBring up to a gentle simmer,\nskimming off any scum that forms on the surface.\n\nSimmer for 35-40 minutes.\n\nRemove from the heat and blend with a hand blender or\nplace into a food processor (allow to cool for 3-4 minutes) and blend until\nsmooth.\n\nPass\nthe puree through a sieve set over the pan, rubbing with the back of a ladle or\nwooden spoon until very smooth and silky.\n\nIf\nit looks a little thick, add more stock to thin it down a little.\n\nReturn the pan over a medium heat and add the cream.\n\nStir well and season, to taste, with salt and black\npepper.\n\nServe garnished with the fresh chives\nand the sour cream on the side.", "ingredients": "Cream (Milk), Modified Starch (gluten Free), Stabilizer (Carrageenan)\nNatural Extra Virgin Olive Oil"}}, {"id": 9125, "name": "Coronation Chicken Salad", "kcal": 157.0, "contains": ["Tree nuts", "Eggs", "Milk", "Celery", "Mustard", "Soya", "Sulphites"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Rub the olive oil all\nover the chicken.\n\nScatter over the lemon\nzest and season with salt and pepper.\n\nSteam the chicken for 8-10\nminutes, or until cooked through.\n\nSet aside to cool.\n\nMelt the butter in a\nfrying pan, add the onion and chili and cook for 5 minutes. Stir in the curry\npowder and cook for 2-3 minutes.\n\nStir in the tomato\npurée and cook for a further minute.\n\nAdd the wine and\nsimmer until the volume of the liquid has reduced by half.\n\nStir in the jam and\nstock, and simmer until the volume of the liquid has reduced by half.\n\nSet aside to cool.\n\nMix the mayonnaise and\nthe crème fraîche together in a bowl, then stir in the curry dressing. Fold in\nthe mango, spring onions, lemon juice and coriander.\n\nCut the chicken into\nbite-sized pieces. Fold into the curry dressing and season with salt, pepper\nand Tabasco to taste.\n\nServe with the lettuce\nand scatter with the toasted almond flakes.", "ingredients": "Cream (Milk), Modified Starch (gluten Free), Stabilizer (Carrageenan)\nCow's Milk Fat, Bacterial Culture\nNatural Extra Virgin Olive Oil"}}, {"id": 9126, "name": "Dugah For Koshari", "kcal": 385.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "in sauce pan, heat the oil add the garlic 