.Pour in coconut milk and bring the mixture to a gentle simmer.Add  tofu, sliced bamboo shoots, halved baby corn, and halved green beans to the pot. Stir well to combine.Season the curry with palm sugar and fish sauce. Stir until the sugar is dissolved.Add mixed vegetables to the pot. Stir well to coat the vegetables with the curry sauce.Cover the pot and let the curry simmer over low heat for about 10-15 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender but still vibrant in color.Once the vegetables are cooked, stir in torn kaffir lime leaves and Thai basil leaves.Taste the curry and adjust the seasoning with salt."}}, {"id": 9248, "name": "Roasted Pumpkin Puree", "kcal": 41.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Wash and peel pumpkin. Remove seeds. Cut pumpkin into large cubes and put in a tray lined with a silicone mat or baking paper.Roast at 170C for 25-30 minutes until very soft.After roasting, blend in a food processor into a puree. Keep in fridge up to 72 hours or freeze for up to 1 month."}}, {"id": 9249, "name": "Garlic Sautéed Snow Peas", "kcal": 90.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Remove and discard the stem end and string from each sugar snap pod.Heat the olive oil in a large sauté pan over medium-high heat. Add the garlic,  sugar snap peas, salt and pepper and sauté, tossing occasionally for 3 to 5 minutes, until the sugar snap peas are crisp tender.Place the sugar snap peas in a serving bowl, sprinkle with  salt and serve."}}, {"id": 9250, "name": "Texas Style Rub Marination for Rib Eye Revised", "kcal": 191.0, "contains": ["Mustard"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a mixing bowl, stir together\nthe water, lemon juice, and brown\nsugar until the sugar is\ncompletely dissolved.\n\n· Add the rub spices.\n\n·Mix well until a thick, even paste forms."}}, {"id": 9251, "name": "Fish Strips Cut", "kcal": 114.0, "contains": ["Fish"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "cut the fish fillet into strips"}}, {"id": 9252, "name": "Tropical Fruit Savarin Revised", "kcal": 196.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Milk"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "For the savarin:Butter the savarin moulds . Shape the savarin dough into 25g balls, then spread them in the savarin moulds using your hands. Let them rise in the proofer at 30 øC for 20 minutes, until the dough has slightly less than doubled in volume. Pre-heat the ovento 160*C  no steam. Put the savarin in the oven at 160øC and leave them to cook for 8 minutes (turn the trays halfway through cooking). Take them out of the oven, remove them from the moulds and put them back in the oven on a baking tray for 5 minutes at 160 øC to brown them. Take the out and leave them to cool.For the syrup and soaking the savarin:Put the savarin to soak in the syrup for 20 minutes, then strain for 20 minutes, before re-soaking them in the syrup. Put them in the chiller for 10 minutes, then apply the neutral glaze to the savarin with a brush and put them to one side on a rack.For the chantilly passion:Brunoise (finely dice) the mangos and the pineapple. Caramelized half of the diced mangoes and pine apple in the olive oil and lemon juice. Deglaze with the passion fruit pulp, add the diced papaya. Leave to cool. Fill the center of each savarin with the mixture. Using a bag fitted with a star piping nozzle, create a rose shape to cover the center of the savarin. Sprinkle with the remaining diced mangos, pineapple and papaya and add a light sprinkling of lime zest to decorate.Serve at room temperature."}}, {"id": 9253, "name": "Savarin Syrup", "kcal": 233.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a Sauce pan add all the  ingredientsBoil it and remove from the fire Ready use."}}, {"id": 9254, "name": "Base Savarin Dough", "kcal": 250.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Milk"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Add all ingredients in a mixing bowlUsing the pedal Until it's become smooth batter.", "ingredients": "Cow's Milk Fat, Bacterial Culture"}}, {"id": 9255, "name": "Garlic Lemon Calamari with Coriander", "kcal": 202.0, "contains": ["Molluscs"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "heat the oil add the garlic and saute until fragrant add the calamari, salt and peppersaute them for 3 minutes on medium heat add the coriander and saute for 1 minute moreremove from heat then pour the lemon juice and mix", "ingredients": "Natural Extra Virgin Olive Oil"}}, {"id": 9256, "name": "Smoked Salmon Diced, Sliced, Chopped. (to be updated)", "kcal": 216.0, "contains": ["Fish"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Cut the smoked salmon as per standard.", "ingredients": "Salmon (Fish), Salt, Sugar, Natural Smoke"}}, {"id": 9257, "name": "Rice for Maklouba", "kcal": 148.0, "contains": ["Celery"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Wash the rice a few times to make sure the starches are removed. Soak in cold water for about 30 minutes.\nin tilting pan, place the broth with the spices bring them to boil, then add the vegetables for maklouba and the soaked rice bring them to boil for 2 minutes, then low the heat and cook them for 10 minutescover the rice with aluminum foil and cook for 10 minutes morethen off the heat and leave it covered for 15 minutesfluff the rice and remove from the pan"}}, {"id": 9258, "name": "Sour Dough Slice", "kcal": 224.0, "contains": ["Gluten"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "sliced the bread into 6pcs. 50g each."}}, {"id": 9259, "name": "Mango Kale Salad", "kcal": 90.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a large bowl, toss the mango, kale, red pepper, green pepper, onion, and cucumber.In a small bowl, whisk together the lemon juice, olive oil, black