all bowl.Season the chicken pieces with salt and pepper on both sides.Arrange the chicken pieces in a single layer in a large baking dish or roasting pan.Pour the marinade over the chicken pieces, ensuring they are evenly coated.Place the lemon slices on top of the chicken pieces.Cover the roasting pan with aluminum foil, and let the chicken marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.Once marinated, remove the aluminum foil from the roasting pan.Bake the chicken in the preheated oven for about 30-40 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and golden brown and the internal temperature reaches at least 75°C for safety.Once cooked, remove the chicken from the oven and let it rest for a few minutes before serving.Serve the Lemon & Thyme Chicken hot, garnished with additional fresh thyme leaves and lemon slices if desired.", "ingredients": "Cow's Milk Fat, Bacterial Culture"}}, {"id": 9265, "name": "Chicken Tagine with Couscous Revised", "kcal": 222.0, "contains": ["Gluten"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Cut all the vegetables in wedges and set asideFried the potato wedges in deep fryer and set aside.Mix all the spices with olive oil, garlic, vinegar and tomato paste, Then cover the chicken with the mixture very well, and keep in chiller for at least 4 hours.Preheat the oven on 180 degree.Arrange the veggies in shallow food pan together and cover with parchment paper and aluminum foil.Baked for 45 to 60 minutes.serve with Steamed Couscous"}}, {"id": 9266, "name": "DEL-1Creamy Chicken White Pasta", "kcal": 136.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Milk"], "may_contain": ["Mustard", "Soya"], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and sear until a golden crust develops, 3-4 minutes per side. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside and let rest for 10 minutes, then cut into strips. Gradually sprinkle the cheese into the alfredo sauce, stirring continuously.Add the cooked pasta and use a spatula to gently toss to incorporate. Add the cooked chicken and toss to combine.If desired, add pasta water, small splashes at a time, and gently toss until desired consistency is reached. (This can be very helpful when reheating leftovers as well, it smooths the sauce back out.)Garnish with parsley."}}, {"id": 9267, "name": "Pastilla Revised", "kcal": 150.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Sulphites"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Turn the oven on to 180*C and adjust a rack in the middle.Prepare a  pie dish  and brush the bottoms and sides with extra virgin olive oil.Take one sheet of phyllo dough and fold it in half vertically . Brush the top of the folded phyllo with extra virgin olive oil. Now lay the folded phyllo sheet in the middle with the sides hanging on either side of the pan. Repeat with more sheets of the phyllo, making sure each sheet is folded and brushed with oil. Layer the phyllo sheets in the pan so that they overlap, rotating the pan so that the phyllo will cover it on all sides (there should be phyllo slack hanging over on all sides of the pan).Spread the chicken mixture over the phyllo. Cover with the remaining sheets of phyllo, making sure to brush each layer with olive oil. Fold the phyllo sides over to cove. Brush the top with extra virgin olive oil.Bake on the center rack of your heated oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until the phyllo is fully cooked and golden brown."}}, {"id": 9268, "name": "Chicken Mixture For Pastilla Revised", "kcal": 76.0, "contains": ["Eggs", "Sulphites"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In the same pan, add the onion slices and garlic, if needed, add a little more olive oil. Season with a good pinch of kosher salt. Cook over medium heat, tossing regularly until softened.\rAdd cup of water and the spices. Bring to a boil, then add the seared chicken pack to the pan. Cook over medium-high heat for about 10 to 15 minutes or until the chicken is fully cooked through and the liquid has reduced by  .\rCarefully remove the chicken from the pan onto a cutting board. Using two forks (or a fork and knife), shred or break the chicken up into small pieces.\rTo the pan of liquid, stir in the beaten eggs. Return the chicken to the pan and stir to combine. Stir in the chopped dry apricot and  coriander. Remove from the heat."}}, {"id": 9269, "name": "Seared Chicken For Pastilla Revised", "kcal": 115.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Pat the chicken dry and season with kosher salt and black pepper on both sides.\rIn a large pan, heat  olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and sear until brown on both sides (about 5 minutes or so). Remove the chicken from the pan and set aside."}}, {"id": 9270, "name": "Chicken Ala King Revised", "kcal": 101.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Milk"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium-high heat.Add in mushroom button and cook until mushrooms are soft, about 5 minutes.Add in flour and stir until there are no more specks of flour left. Pour in milk, heavy cream and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to lowand simmer until sauce is thickened, about 3 minutes.Stir in green peas, red and green bell peppers, boneless skinless chicken breast cube and let heat through, 2 to 3 minutes.Season with salt and ground white pepper.", "ingredients": "Fresh Cream (Milk), Fresh Cow's Milk, Milk Solids, Stabilizers (E401, E516, E450, E331), Vitamin D3.\nCow's Milk Fat, Bacterial Culture"}}, {"id": 9271, "name": "Peruvian Chicken With Creamy Green Sauce Revised", "kcal": 232.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Mustard", "Soya"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Preheat  grill to medium-high heat.Grill the marinated chicken pieces, turning occasionally, until they are cooked through and nicely charred on the outside. This usually takes about 20-25 minutes, depending on the size and thickness of the chicken pieces.Once the chicken is cooked through, remove it from the grill and transfer it to a serving platter.Serve the grilled Peruvian chicken with creamy green sauce on the side for dipping or drizzling."}}, {"id": 9272, "name": "Nasi Ayam Revised", "kcal": 144.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Milk", "Crustaceans", "Molluscs", "Celery", "Soya", "Sulphites"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Pre-heat the oven for 180 Degree Celsius place the marinated chicken on oven tray and bake for 40 minutes or until cookedto serve the Nasi ayam: scoop the rice in serving plateslice the chicken and place them aside the riceserve with the broth, sambal asideserve sliced tomatoes and cucumber aside"}}, {"id": 9273, "name": "Chicken Marinade for Nasi Ayam Revised", "kcal": 171.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Molluscs", "Celery", "Soya", "Sulphites"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "in steel bowl, place all the ingredients mix them well and let it marinate for at least 6 hours", "ingredients": "Pepper, Sugar, Salt, Garlic, Preservatives: E260 (Acetic Acid), E202 (Potassium Sorbate), E222 (Sodium Bisulfite), Thickener: E415 (Xanthan Gum)"}}, {"id": 9274, "name": "Pollo Al Carbon Revised", "kcal": 239.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.Remove the chicken from the marinade, allowing any excess marinade to drip off.Grill the chicken pieces, turning occasionally, until they are cooked through and the juices run clear, about 20-25 minutes for smaller pieces and 30-40 minutes for larger pieces.While grilling, baste the chicken occasionally with any remaining marinade to keep it moist and flavorful.Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a serving platter and garnish with lime wedges and cilantro."}}, {"id": 9275, "name": "Chicken Enchilada Filling Revised", "kcal": 256.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": ["Gluten"], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a small bowl, combine oil, lime juice, chili powder, cumin, oregano, salt, and garlic powder. Whisk to combine. Place minced chicken into a bowl and pour the marinade mixture over the top. Mix well to coat all of the chicken. Please leave it to marinate for an hour. Heat a medium skillet on medium heat.Add olive oil. Once the oil is hot, add the marinated ground chicken. Bread the meat. After 1 or 2 minutes, add onion and stir to combine.Sauté until chicken is golden brown and cooked through and onion is soft, about 6-7 minutes.Add the chopped garlic, stir, and cook for one minute. Add water, black pepper powder, and salt. Cook another 1-2 minutes, and Stir and turn the heat off."}}, {"id": 9276, "name": "Chicken Burrito Revised", "kcal": 144.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Milk", "Celery", "Sulphites"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Preheat oven to 180*C.\rWarm the tortillas in the microwave for about 30 seconds. Warming them up simply makes them more pliable and easy to fold\rLayer them with Mexican rice, chicken burritos filling, corn, cheese and then fold them up burrito style.\rToast them in the oven for 10 minutes, wrapped in foil, or pan fry over medium-high heat for 2 minutes per side until the tortilla is crispy and the cheese melts.", "ingredients": "Corn"}}, {"id": 9277, "name": "Riza Djej (Oriental chicken Rice) Revised", "kcal": 133.0, "contains": ["Celery"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Wash the rice and make sure you drain it really well. \rAdd some oil to a non-stick pan and saut  the chopped onions and minced meat. \rMix in the allspice, seven spices, ground cinnamon,  salt, and rice. Cook everything together for a minute. Add chicken broth to the  the rice mixture. Bring everything to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and cover. Cook until the rice is done (about 8 to 10 minutes). \rOnce the rice is done, add a layer of shredded chicken"}}, {"id": 9278, "name": "Braised Chicken With Mushroom & Root Vegetables Revised", "kcal": 92.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Celery"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Preheat the oven to 180*C.Braise in the pot to the  oven for about 1.5 to 2 hours, or until the chicken is tender and cooked through, and the vegetables are soft.Once done, remove the pot from the oven and skim off any excess fat from the surface of the sauce.Taste and adjust the seasoning with salt and pepper.Garnished with chopped parsley."}}, {"id": 9279, "name": "Chicken And Vegetable Mixture For Braised Chicken With Mushroom & Root Vegetable Revised", "kcal": 90.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Celery"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Heat oil in pan.\rAdd the diced onions, celery, and leeks to the pot. Cook until softened, about 5-7 minutes.\rStir in the minced garlic and cook for another minute until fragrant.\rAdd the tomato paste and cook for a few minutes to deepen the flavor.\rReturn the chicken pieces and crispy bacon to the pot. Add the sliced mushrooms, carrots, potatoes, parsnips, turnips, fresh thyme leaves, and chopped parsley.\rPour in enough chicken broth to cover all the ingredients.\rBring the mixture to a simmer, then cover the pot."}}, {"id": 9280, "name": "Browned Chicken For Braised Chicken With Mushroom & Root Vegetable Revised", "kcal": 235.0, "contains": ["Gluten"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a large Dutch oven or heavy-bottomed pot, heat some olive oil over medium-high heat.\rSeason the chicken pieces with salt and pepper, then dust them with flour, shaking off any excess.\rBrown the chicken pieces in batches until golden brown on all sides. Remove and set aside.", "ingredients": "Wheat Flour, Mixture Of Iron And Vitamins (Thiamin, Riboflavin, Niacin, Vitamin D, Folic Acid)"}}, {"id": 9281, "name": "Crispy Chicken Bun Revised", "kcal": 229.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Milk", "Mustard", "Soya"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Cook chicken as per sub recipe,Slice Brioche in 1/2.Spread mayonnaise.place 180 g cg=hicken on roll and top with rest of Roll"}}, {"id": 9282, "name": "Chicksilog Revised", "kcal": 163.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Soya"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Cut chicken whole by quarter and seasoned with salt, pepper soy sauce.In a frying pan, deep fried chicken for 8-12 minutes or until cooked In a plate arrange a bowl of garlic rice (turn upside down) a piece of quarter fried chicken and a piece of fried egg. Garnish with slice cucumber and slice tomato on the side"}}, {"id": 9283, "name": "Chicken Pot Au Feu Revised", "kcal": 151.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Celery"], "may_contain": ["Sulphites", "Lupin"], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "IN a large pot add Chicken,carrots,potatoes,leeks,celery,onions,turnips,parsnips,mushrooms,green beans,Pearl Barley,Minced Garlic,Pepper,amd thyme.add enough water to cover all ingreients with 2 inch over the top.on medium heat bring to a simmer and gently simmer for 90 to 120 minutes.when cihicen is soft and vegetables arecooked skim off any foam .remove chicken from pot and put aside.remove vegetables from broth with slotted spoon. and place on serving Dish.strain broth through muslin Cloth and discard solids.season broth to taste arrange chicken and vegetables and ladle broth over.Garnish with chopped parsley"}}, {"id": 9284, "name": "Potato - Chicken Fajita Revised", "kcal": 173.0, "contains": ["Milk"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Carefully unwrap the potatoes.\n \n \n  Cut a slit\n  in the top and fluff the insides with a fork. Fill with chicken fajitas inside and topped with cheese Put in salamander or oven for 2 minutes until the cheese melted, Serve with required condiments as per menu or the Guest choices."}}, {"id": 9285, "name": "Miso Marinated Chicken Revised", "kcal": 191.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Soya"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "in bowl, place the chicken \rpour the marinade over the chicken \rmassage the chicken into the cavity and skin\rlet it marinate for at least 12 hours in refrigerator"}}, {"id": 9286, "name": "Chicken Panaeng Curry copy", "kcal": 161.0, "contains": ["Peanuts", "Fish"], "may_contain": ["Tree nuts"], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a large pot , heat vegetable oil over medium heat. Add minced garlic, minced ginger, and minced lemongrass. Sauté until fragrant.Add Panaeng curry paste to the pot. Stir-fry for 2-3 minutes until the paste is fragrant and the oil starts to separate.Add chicken pieces to the pot. Cook until the chicken is no longer pink on the outside.Pour in coconut milk and bring the mixture to a gentle simmer.Add sliced green beans, red bell pepper, and bamboo shoots to the pot. Stir well to combine.Season the curry with palm sugar and fish sauce. Stir until the sugar is dissolved.Add torn kaffir lime leaves to the pot. Stir well to incorporate.Cover the pot and let the curry simmer over low heat for 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is cooked through and the vegetables are tender.Once the chicken is cooked, taste the curry and adjust the seasoning if necessary.Stir in Thai basil leaves and crushed roasted peanuts. Cook for another minute."}}, {"id": 9287, "name": "Buffalo Chicken Wings Revised", "kcal": 191.0, "contains": ["Gluten"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "in Frying pan, place the chicken and buffalo sauce mix together until combined", "ingredients": "Distilled Vinegar, Aged Cayenne Red Peppers, Salt, Water, Canola Oil, Paprika, Xanthan Gum (Thickener), Garlic Powder, Natural Flavor"}}, {"id": 9288, "name": "Chicken Machboos Revised", "kcal": 189.0, "contains": ["Milk", "Celery"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "wash the rice good and soak by cold water for 1 hourin pan, heat the ghee add the cinnamon sticks, cardamom, cloves, whole black pepper and dry lemon sauté for 1 minutes until fragrant add the onion and garlic and stir for 2 minutes add the tomatoes and spices and sauté for 5 minutes on low heatadd the chicken broth and salt bring the water to boil then strain the rice and add it to the broth keep the rice on high heat until start boiling, then reduce the heat, cover the pan by aluminum foil and cook for about 30 minutes on low heat off the heat and keep in pan for 10 minutes morePre-heat the oven on 180 Degreearrange the chicken in oven tray and bake for about 50 minutes until cook transfer the rice to serving GN and place the chicken on top"}}, {"id": 9289, "name": "Creole Chicken Revised", "kcal": 223.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Milk"], "may_contain": ["Celery"], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Heat oil in a pan, add the onion and green pepper. Sauté until the onion is translucent, around 5 minutes. Add the creole seasoning and stir constantly for 30 seconds.Mix in the flour and stir for another 30 seconds.Add 1/2 cup chicken stock and stir constantly, scraping up any flour on the bottom of the pan. The sauce will thicken considerably. Add 1 1/2 cups of stock and bring to a boil. Return chicken skin side up along with any accumulated juices to the pot. Check to see the liquid comes to about half way up the chicken. If it doesn't, add a bit more stock.Simmer covered for 12 minutes. Flip the chicken and simmer until done, another 12-15 minutes. Remove chicken from the pot, increase the heat and reduce slightly.Remove from heat and mix in the whipping cream.Taste and adjust salt.", "ingredients": "Wheat Flour, Mixture Of Iron And Vitamins (Thiamin, Riboflavin, Niacin, Vitamin D, Folic Acid)\nSALT, DRIED RED CHILI PEPPER, BLACK PEPPER, CHILI POWDER (CHILI PEPPER, SPICES, SALT, GARLIC POWDER), DEHYDRATED GARLIC, SILICON DIOXIDE (ANTI CAKING AGENT)\nSalt, Maltodextrin, Corn Starch (Dehydrated Chicken Meat And Chicken Fat, Sugar, Yeast Extract, Disodium Isonate, Disodium Guanylate, Flavour, Silicon Dioxide, Spices, Citric Acid\nMay Contain: Celery"}}, {"id": 9290, "name": "Fried Chicken Thighs For Creole Chicken Revised", "kcal": 226.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Season the chicken thighs generously with creole seasoning. Heat the oil until it shimmers in a dutch oven large enough to hold all the chicken. Notice how much oil is in the pan.\rFry the chicken skin side down over medium heat until golden - 4 to 5 minutes. Turn the chicken over and fry another 3-4 minutes.\rRemove chicken. Set Aside.", "ingredients": "SALT, DRIED RED CHILI PEPPER, BLACK PEPPER, CHILI POWDER (CHILI PEPPER, SPICES, SALT, GARLIC POWDER), DEHYDRATED GARLIC, SILICON DIOXIDE (ANTI CAKING AGENT)"}}, {"id": 9291, "name": "Chicken Quesadillas Revised", "kcal": 198.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Milk"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Heat a 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium or medium-low heat. Add a touch of oil to the pan for a crispier quesadilla. Cook the quesadillas on one side until golden, moderating the heat as needed, pressing lightly with a spatula to compress and flatten a bit. Carefully flip the quesadillas with the spatula and cook on the other side until the tortilla is golden and the filling and cheese is hot and melted.Cut into triangles and serve immediately."}}, {"id": 9292, "name": "Quesadillas For Chicken Quesadillas Revised", "kcal": 187.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Milk"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat the oil over medium heat. Add the mushrooms, onions, and bell peppers. Cook, stirring often, until the onions start to turn translucent and the vegetables start to soften.\rAdd 2-3 tablespoons water. Continue cooking over medium heat for 2-3 minutes until the veggies are crisp-tender and the liquid has reduced slightly.\rAssemble the quesadillas by spreading cheese on 1/2 of each tortilla. Top the cheese with chicken, veggies, more cheese, and then fold the tortilla in half over the filling ingredients.", "ingredients": "Wheat Flour (71%), Water, Vegetable Fat (palm Oil), Glucose (from Wheat), Salt 0.6%, Acidity Regulator: E296 (malic Acid), Raising Agent E500 (sodium Carbonate), Emulsifier: E471 (mono And Diglycerides) Curing Agent: E920 (L Cysteine\nPasteurized Cow Milk, Cheese (Milk) Culture, Salt, Fungi Rennet (Chymax), Color (Beta Carotene)"}}, {"id": 9293, "name": "Spiced Chicken For Chicken Quesadillas Revised", "kcal": 159.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a small bowl, add all the seasoning ingredients. Mix well.\rToss the chicken with 1/2 of the seasoning mixture. Set aside."}}, {"id": 9294, "name": "Cooked Chicken Breast Revised", "kcal": 155.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a frying pan add the olive oil and let heat for few minutes. Then add the chicken diced sauté for 10 minutes. When chicken is cooked add salt and pepper to taste. Remove from heat, and set aside for later use."}}, {"id": 9295, "name": "Tandoori Chicken Revised", "kcal": 165.0, "contains": ["Milk"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.Grill the chicken for a total of 25 to 30 minutes. Basting with melted butter after the first 12 to 15 minutes.Turn the chicken to the other side after Basting and grill for another 12 to 15 minutes, followed by 2 to 3 minutes of broiling to get some charred spots. When the chicken is cooked through, brush the  melted butter all over the chicken to keep it moist. Garnish with chopped coriander leaves.", "ingredients": "Cow's Milk Fat, Bacterial Culture"}}, {"id": 9296, "name": "Marinated Chicken For Chicken Tandoori Revised", "kcal": 182.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Add chicken thigh  to the marinade and coat them well.Refrigerate overnight."}}, {"id": 9297, "name": "Cooked Chicken For Kong Pao Chicken Revised", "kcal": 186.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Sesame", "Soya", "Sulphites"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Heat a large skillet pan over high heat. Add cooking oil, allow to heat up, then add marinated chicken. Fry chicken for 3-4 minutes while occasionally stirring, until edges are browned. Remove from heat and set aside."}}, {"id": 9298, "name": "Marinated Chicken for Kung Pao Chicken Revised", "kcal": 105.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Sesame", "Soya", "Sulphites"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Mix corn startch with water.dd al other ingredients and mix. place in chiller for 3-5 hours"}}, {"id": 9299, "name": "Chicken Jareesh Revised", "kcal": 179.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Milk", "Celery"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Wash and Soak the Jareesh at least for 2 hours in pot, place the gheesautee the onion and the dry lemon until fragrantadd the garlic and saute for 2 minutes moredrain the jareesh and add it to the onion and garlicsaute them for about 3 minutes then add the chicken broth add the pulled chicken and black peppercook them on low heat for about 2 hours (keep stirring them to did not stick in pot)once the jareesh cooked properly add the milk and cook them for 10 minutes moreadjust the salt if needed Serve with Mussamanah", "ingredients": "Fresh Cow's Milk, Vitamin A, Vitamin D3."}}, {"id": 9300, "name": "Poached Turkey Breast Revised", "kcal": 186.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "on oven tray, arrange the turkey breast steam in oven for about 14 minutes or until cook"}}, {"id": 9301, "name": "Marinated Chicken For Spicy Fried Korean Chicken Revised", "kcal": 200.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Molluscs", "Celery", "Sesame", "Soya"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "In a large bowl, add the chicken and all the ingredients for the marinade. Mix all this together.Cover and leave this in your fridge for at least an hour or you can leave it overnight."}}, {"id": 9302, "name": "Lemon Thyme Chicken/Carving Station Revised", "kcal": 269.0, "contains": [], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Preheat oven to 185*C\rPlace the chicken in a roasting pan lined with parchment paper.\rRoast the chicken in the preheated oven for about 1 to 1.5 hours, depending on the chicken's size, until the internal temperature reaches 75 C in the thickest part of the meat or until the juices run clear when pierced with a fork.\rIf the chicken starts to brown too quickly, you can cover it loosely with aluminum foil to prevent overbrowning.\rOnce the chicken is cooked, please remove it from the oven and let it rest for about 10 minutes before carving."}}, {"id": 9303, "name": "Chicken Schnitzel Revised", "kcal": 724.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs"], "may_contain": [], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Fry the breaded chicken in batches, flipping once, untilgolden brown, 2 to 3 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack set over a baking sheet to drain; season both sides with salt and pepper. ."}}, {"id": 9304, "name": "Chicken & Mushroom Lasagna", "kcal": 204.0, "contains": ["Gluten", "Eggs", "Milk", "Celery"], "may_contain": ["Mustard", "Soya"], "source": "recipes", "details": {"method": "Preheat oven to 180°CIn a baking dish. Smear a bit of chicken Bolognese and sautéed mushrooms on the base, then cover with lasagna sheets. Tear sheets to fit. Spread over the chicken Bolognese and sautéed mushrooms (enough to cover sheets), then drizzle over of Béchamel Sauce.Top with lasagna sheets. Spread with another of chicken Bolognese, and sautéed mushrooms then béchamel Sauce. Top with lasagna sheets then repeat 1 more time.Top with a last layer of lasagna sheets, then pour over the remaining Béchamel Sauce. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and parmesan cheese, then bake for 25 minutes or until golden and bubbling."}}]
